com.i2group.disco.infostore.importer

Class RetrievalBlockDataGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.disco.infostore.importer.RetrievalBlockDataGenerator

  • public final class RetrievalBlockDataGenerator
extends Object
    Generates values for the RETRIEVAL_BLOCK_DATA columns of provenance tables in the Information Store, from values in the RETRIEVAL_BLOCK_TEMPLATE column of the INGESTION_SOURCES table.

    This class has a runtime dependency on the Jackson data binding project, http://wiki.fasterxml.com/JacksonHome.

    Since:
    9.0

    • Constructor Detail

      • RetrievalBlockDataGenerator

        public RetrievalBlockDataGenerator(String retrievalBlockTemplate)
        Constructs a new RetrievalBlockDataGenerator.
        Parameters:
        retrievalBlockTemplate - A String that contains the value from the RETRIEVAL_BLOCK_TEMPLATE column of the INGESTION_SOURCES table for the ingestion source that a particular record comes from. This parameter can be null.

    • Method Detail

      • getRequiredColumnsForTemplate

        public Set<String> getRequiredColumnsForTemplate()
        Gets Strings that contain the names of the columns whose data is required for building the retrieval block data. If there is no retrieval block template, or the template does not contain column references, then the list is empty.
        Returns:
        See above.

      • generateRetrievalBlockData

        public String generateRetrievalBlockData(Map<String,String> columnValuesByColumnName)
        Generates a String value for use in the RETRIEVAL_BLOCK_DATA column of a provenance table in the Information Store, based on the specified values for any columns that a retrieval block template requires.
        Parameters:
        columnValuesByColumnName - The String values for the template from the current row, keyed by their column name.
        Returns:
        See above, or null if there is no retrieval block template, or the template does not contain column references.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If columnValuesByColumnName is null, or any of its values are null, or it does not contain an entry for each column named by getRequiredColumnsForTemplate().
        IllegalStateException - If there is an error during value creation.
